lical business community and the New Deal-and in doing so makes important contributions to American religious history, business history, and the history of the American state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aBusinessxReligious aspectsxProtestant churches. 0aCapitalismxReligious aspectsxProtestant churches. 0aChristianityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aEvangelicalismxEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aEvangelicalismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 4aConservatism. 4aEntrepreneurialism. 4aEvangelicalism. 4aFundamentalism. 4aNew Deal. 4aPolitics. 4aReligion. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aDochuk, Darren, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226509808423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226509808.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles